## <a id='rotate'></a> Rotating credentials

The <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) tile handles all of the credentials for <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>.

To rotate your credentials in <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>, you must redeploy <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> and <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>. To re-deploy <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> and <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>:

1. Go to the VMware Tanzu Operations Manager Installation Dashboard.

1. Click **Review Pending Changes**.

1. Click the <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> and <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %> tiles and review the changes.

   For more information, see [Reviewing pending product changes](https://docs.pivotal.io/ops-manager/2-10/install/review-pending-changes.html).

2. Click **Apply Changes**.

## <a id='upgrade-tile'></a> Upgrading <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>

To upgrade <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>:

1. Download the latest <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %> version from the [<%= vars.windows_runtime_full %>](https://network.tanzu.vmware.com/products/pas-windows/) page on <%= vars.product_network %>.

   For more information about upgrading your <%= vars.platform_name %> products,
   see [Upgrading <%= vars.platform_name %> products](https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-Tanzu-Operations-Manager/3.0/vmware-tanzu-ops-manager/install-upgrading-products.html#other-products)
   in _Upgrading <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> and Other <%= vars.platform_name %> Products_.

1. If necessary, configure the product.

   For more information about configuring <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>, see [Installing and configuring <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %>](./installing.html).

2. Click **Review Pending Changes**.

3. Click the <%= vars.windows_runtime_abbr %> tile and review the changes. For more information, see [Reviewing pending product changes](https://docs.pivotal.io/ops-manager/2-10/install/review-pending-changes.html).

4. Click **Apply Changes**.

## <a id='upgrade-stemcell'></a> Upgrading the Windows stemcell

To upgrade your Windows stemcell:

1. Retrieve the stemcell by following the steps for your IaaS (infrastructure as a service):
   * For vSphere, you must build your own stemcell. For more information, see the [BOSH documentation](https://bosh.io/docs/windows-stemcell-create/).
   * For AWS, GCP, and Azure, go to [Stemcells (Windows)](https://network.pivotal.io/products/stemcells-windows-server) on <%= vars.product_network %>.

2. Go to **Stemcell Library**.

3. Click **Import Stemcell** to import the stemcell file.

4. Activate the Tanzu Operations Manager product check box to stage your stemcell.

5. Click **Apply Stemcell to Products**.

For more information about Windows stemcells, see [Downloading or creating Windows stemcells](stemcells.html).
